&gt; I primarily am using Franks method as first of all, its hard to hear my own questions being asked, and secondly, my own voice seems to &quot;walk over&quot; some potntially good stuff.  So I say my peice at the beginning of the tape---time/date and a request and let the entities then take over on their own.
&gt; 
&gt; I attribute the sentances to the 25 inch long, 2 inch PVC pipe I use as a resonator.  Set the loudspeaker of your radio on one end and record from the other.  If you want, do what I did and cut a slot on the side of the pipe just big enough to insert your speaker or speaker end of the radio and have it as a single unit.  I think the pipe approximates the resonance of a human vocal tract and also can pick up environmental sounds--all for the use of the entity.  not to mention reduce the &quot;spikey-ness&quot; of the radio scanner sounds and thus produce a more continious carrier wave.
